original: Huss, Rolf Harald, landsfiskal, Ske-ne, f. 28/4/06 i Uddevalla av bokför. E. W. Huss o. Edith Broberg. G. 33 m. Ingegerd Fredrikson. Barn: Per-Äke f. 35. — Realex. 23, landsfiskals-ex. 30. Tf. o. ord. landskanslist v. länsstyr. i Vänersborg 29-41, lands-fiskalsassist. i Bengtsfors’ distr. 41-45, landsfiskal i Skene distr. sed. 46.
translated: Huss, Rolf Harald, district attorney, Skene, born on April 28th, 1906 in Uddevalla to bookkeeper E.W. Huss and Edith Broberg. Married in 1933 to Ingegerd Fredrikson, with one child named Per-Äke, born in 1935. Rolf completed his Realexamen (similar to high school diploma) in 1923, and his district attorney exam in 1930. He was temporarily and then permanently employed as a district clerk at the County Government in Vänersborg from 1929 to 1941. From 1941 to 1945, he worked as a district attorney assistant in the Bengtsfors district, and from 1946 onwards, he was a district attorney in the Skene district.
